			<p>Why not just use px to reset the text size for the body? </p>
<p>body {<br />
     10px;<br />
}</p>
<p>Then, use percents for the rest.</p>
<p>p {<br />
font-size: 110%;<br />
}</p>
<p>Oh, and did you know that you should not use units for line-height? See <a href="http://meyerweb.com/eric/thoughts/2006/02/08/unitless-line-heights/" rel="nofollow">http://meyerweb.com/eric/thoughts/2006/02/08/unitless-line-heights/</a> for the long explanation.</p>

